## Philadelphia Park System Story Map

This story map introduces the evolution of Philadelphia's park system, exploring its historical development from the 17th century to the present day. The map combines narrative text with geographic data to highlight significant moments in the cityâ€™s park history, such as the establishment of Fairmount Park and the modern green initiatives. This project is intended for urban planners, students of urban development, and residents of Philadelphia interested in the history and future of their public spaces.

### Data Sources:
[OpenDataPhilly for park boundaries and historical landmarks](https://opendataphilly.org/)
Historical records from the Philadelphia Historical Society.
